/* Words To Live By: Part One — fetched from thevolumesoftruth.com */
var WTLB_ONE = [{"id":"introduction","num":1,"title":"Introduction","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"**WORDS TO LIVE BY...**\n\n\n\n_**More Words of Wisdom**_\n\n_**From The Lord, Our God and Savior**_\n\n\n\n\nFor all those who have dedicated\n\nThemselves to Me by means of The Truth,\n\nThose who have recognized My words\n\nAnd also do them...\n\n\n\nThose who came to Me empty\n\nThat I might fill them up,\n\nThat they might be truly dedicated to Me...\n\n\n\nEven as I had dedicated Myself to them also,\n\nThat we may become one...\n\n\n\nSet apart in My glory, for My glory,\n\nTo the joy of their Father in Heaven...\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."},{"align":"justify","text":"Behold, My words shall never pass away. For as I am, so also is My Word. For it proceeds from Me, being manifest by He Who Is True, also being called The Word... Living... Always feeding His flock The Word, which is written for their nourishment, which is to be received through that part of Himself which is also in Me, says The Lord God. ~ [From “The Word of My Mouth” ~ Volume 7]"},{"align":"center","text":"It is written:\n\n\n\n“Man shall not live by bread alone,\n\nBut by every word that proceeds\n\nFrom the mouth of God.”\n\n\n\n{{ref:Matthew 4:4}}"}]},{"id":"come-love-awaits-you","num":2,"title":"Come, Love Awaits You","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Come, all those who know not My ways; I will show you."},{"align":"center","text":"Come, all those who have been abandoned;\n\nI will comfort you and give you shelter."},{"align":"center","text":"Come, all those who are crippled;\n\nLet us run and leap for joy together!"},{"align":"center","text":"Come, all those faithless;\n\nI shall fill your cup, and watch how it overflows!"},{"align":"center","text":"Come, all murderers;\n\nWatch Me raise you, and all who sleep, from the grave."},{"align":"center","text":"Come, all you who blaspheme, I will give you a new voice;\n\nBring with you all those who are blind and deaf,\n\nFor they too shall see and hear!"},{"align":"center","text":"Indeed, come all those who have sinned against Me, take My hand!\n\nI will lead you to the waters where I shall wash you,\n\nAnd where your new clothes hang upon the tree\n\nWhich grows next to the stream."},{"align":"center","text":"Come one, come all! Ask, and it shall be given you!\n\nFor all things are possible with God\n\nAnd made manifest through The Son...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"crowning-glory","num":3,"title":"Crowning Glory","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"The love of God is His crowning glory..."},{"align":"center","text":"And that love is revealed in the glory of The Son,\n\nBy which His beloved are also crowned."}]},{"id":"the-spirit-of-truth-brings-conviction","num":4,"title":"The Spirit of Truth Brings Conviction","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"This question was asked of The Lord, regarding {{ref:Luke 15:11-32}} Lord, have I become hard like the older son? Have I put my hand to tasks, and forgotten to build up compassion for those who have gone astray? Is this story meant to convict me, Lord?"},{"align":"center","text":"[The Lord answered]"},{"align":"center","text":"If your heart is convicted,\n\nThen has it not also given answer\n\nTo your prayer already,\n\nRevealing the Spirit which dwells\n\nWithin you, of what sort it is?"},{"align":"center","text":"For only the Spirit of Truth will bring forth\n\nConviction unto righteousness,\n\nBearing much fruit in The Beloved...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-first-stitch","num":5,"title":"The First Stitch","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"The first stitch, to mend any rent,\n\nAre the words “I’m sorry”...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"yahuwah-is-one-and-his-word-one","num":6,"title":"YAHUWAH Is One; And His Word, One","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"The Old Testament is The Father revealing Himself, while pointing to The Son. The New Testament is The Son revealing Himself while pointing to The Father, also fulfilling the Messianic prophecies of the Old Testament in Himself. The Letters are The Father and The Son revealing themselves as One, even as the Word of God is one, with The Letters being the culmination of the whole - not separate, but one."},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore, to reject any part of\n\nThe Lord’s Word is to reject the whole."},{"align":"center","text":"The three books are one..."},{"align":"center","text":"One on-going testament to God’s glory."}]},{"id":"removing-the-veil","num":7,"title":"Removing The Veil","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"_Thus says The Lord:_ Those who receive of Me begin to see with eyes wide open, with the deafness of their ears healing quickly.\n\nYet those who have not received rely upon the spirit of men to discern, and stumble greatly; rejecting My Word spoken to this generation, while at the same time polluting My Word from aforetime; firmly securing the veil which remains atop their heads, covering their faces in an attempt to hide their shame."},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore, I have spoken it and shall\n\nSay it again before this perverse\n\nAnd most wicked generation,\n\nThough they can in no wise bear to hear it..."},{"align":"center","text":"I AM COME! THE TIME IS HERE!"},{"align":"center","text":"And behold I, The Lord your God,\n\nWill do nothing until I have revealed\n\nMy plans to My servants, the prophets,\n\nAnd this I have done."}]},{"id":"serving-others-in-love","num":8,"title":"Serving Others in Love","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Beloved, by serving others in love,\n\nPutting their needs before your own..."},{"align":"center","text":"By sacrificing yourself,\n\nYour desires, your wants, your will,\n\nYour body, even your very life..."},{"align":"center","text":"Will you learn what it truly means\n\nTo wash each other’s feet,\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"prayers-of-the-sincere-in-heart","num":9,"title":"Prayers of the Sincere in Heart","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Prayer request: Please pray that pride won’t become an issue for me, because I just wanna walk with YahuShua only."},{"align":"center","text":"[The Lord answered]"},{"align":"center","text":"In your request is wisdom;\n\nFor those of a sincere heart,\n\nWhose prayer is to flee from pride,\n\nHave received of their request\n\nAlready in the asking..."},{"align":"center","text":"Whereby they have also begun\n\nTo build up a hedge about themselves,\n\nBecause of their intent...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"touching-the-heart-of-god","num":10,"title":"Touching the Heart of God","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"The hard of heart have no knowledge;\n\nEven all revelation is hidden from their eyes."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet one who shares in My cup,\n\nWeeping heavily upon My chest,\n\nHas touched the heart of God."},{"align":"center","text":"For sincere tears open the door to My fullness,\n\nYet a hard heart is a locked door...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"matters-of-the-heart","num":11,"title":"Matters of the Heart","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"The wailing of the penitent\n\nBrings forth healing;\n\nYet the words of the wicked\n\nCause only pain.\n\n\n\nLove flows outward from\n\nThe hearts of the righteous;\n\nYet the love of the wicked\n\nGrows cold, as hate enters in."}]},{"id":"what-is-pure","num":12,"title":"What Is Pure?","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Giving thanks to God\n\nIn My name is pure worship,\n\nYet the wicked man\n\nDemands honor for himself."},{"align":"center","text":"The heart of a child is pure,\n\nYet the heart of the mature is corrupt...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"the-spirit-of-unity","num":13,"title":"The Spirit of Unity","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"The spirit of unity is in Me, walking in My footsteps, doing unto others as you would have them do unto you; remembering that all you do to others, whether good or bad, you have done also to Me.\n\nHave I not spoken to this already, in the Gospel of My servant, John? For I said to love one another, and to wash each other’s feet, and that you can do nothing apart from Me."},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore be one in Me,\n\nEven as I long to be one with you,\n\nEven as The Father and I are One,\n\nThat our love may be made perfect in One..."},{"align":"center","text":"You in Me, I in you,\n\nTo the joy of The Father...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"a-wise-guide","num":14,"title":"A Wise Guide","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"One who endeavors to teach My flock,\n\nUsing the Word of My own mouth,\n\nMust grow very wise in the hearing\n\nAnd must be wide awake in the Spirit..."},{"align":"center","text":"Discerning, says The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-true-jew","num":15,"title":"The True Jew","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"This question was asked: What is the definition of a true Jew?\n\n\n\n[The Lord answered] The definition of a true Jew is this: YahuShua. Therefore, all those in whom I dwell are Jews indeed. For they are true, even as I am true... _Let none, therefore, bring even one railing accusation against MY olive tree! Says The Lord._"}]},{"id":"finishing-the-race","num":16,"title":"Finishing the Race","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"It is the man who endures through the pain,\n\nAnd perseveres through every obstacle,\n\nWho finishes the race."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet the man who surrenders all to The Lord\n\nWill fly with eagle’s wings."}]},{"id":"dual-paths","num":17,"title":"Dual Paths","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Let those who do wickedly\n\nWalk in the way they have chosen,\n\nUntil their foot becomes ensnared."},{"align":"center","text":"And let those who are Mine seek\n\nRighteousness apart from the wicked,\n\nUntil they are lifted up,\n\nHigh upon healing wings!...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"leading-others-in-righteousness","num":18,"title":"Leading Others in Righteousness","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Can any man lead while wielding a whip?"},{"align":"center","text":"Yet The Lord is above all."}]},{"id":"grace-to-the-humble","num":19,"title":"Grace to the Humble","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Behold, The Lord raises His voice\n\nWithin the hearts of the elect!\n\nYet His silence bears witness\n\nAgainst those who refuse to hear.\n\n\n\nPride is a veil held fast\n\nOver the heads of the arrogant;\n\nIt shall cover them in the day of darkness.\n\nYet the way of the elect is a crown of glory,\n\nAnd grace covers them."}]},{"id":"i-know-my-own","num":20,"title":"I Know My Own","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Those who are Mine receive of Me. For I know My own, and they seek Me; My bride is chosen. Yet those who reject Me and My Word have not known Me, nor will they receive; My spirit is far removed.\n\nThose who set themselves apart from Me, whether by word or deed or by pretense, their hearts are revealed; these shall be left to walk through very dry places. Yet those who seek Me in truth shall be drawn in quickly, whether they are near or far, for I know My own. And those who are married unto Me shall surely enter in.\n\nTherefore, judge no more by human standards, discern by right standards, according to My love and the knowledge you have received in Me."},{"align":"center","text":"For I AM THE LORD, whose will is set\n\nAnd can in no wise be turned back;\n\nEven from the beginning,\n\nIt was decided and accomplished."},{"align":"center","text":"For I AM..."},{"align":"center","text":"And My bride has always been\n\nPredestined in The Beloved,\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"strength-in-weakness","num":21,"title":"Strength in Weakness","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"A man’s strength is revealed\n\nIn confronting his greatest weakness,\n\nYet a man’s greatest strength\n\nBecomes his enemy\n\nWhen pride enters in."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet My strength is made perfect\n\nIn My servant’s weakness...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"stop-lying-to-your-children","num":22,"title":"Stop Lying to Your Children","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"(Regarding Santa, the Easter Bunny, the Tooth Fairy and the like)"},{"align":"justify","text":"No lie is of the Truth. Yet the little ones are of The Truth, and remain with Me and in Me. Even now I call to them, for My lambs know My voice. And that which came from Me must soon return to Me."},{"align":"justify","text":"Therefore, be separate from the ways of this world, and order your conduct according to The Word of Truth. And no more speak lies to your children, for this is sin."},{"align":"center","text":"Rather feed them with The Bread\n\nWhich came down from Heaven,\n\nThe Bread which I am,\n\nThe Way, The Truth, The Life;\n\nFor this alone is pleasing to God."},{"align":"center","text":"Anything to the contrary\n\nIs of the world and the evil one,\n\nNo matter its disguise...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"all-i-have-is-yours","num":23,"title":"All I Have Is Yours...","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"For in knowing Me you possess all things...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-only-fountain-of-knowledge","num":24,"title":"The Only Fountain of Knowledge","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"That which is revealed to one may not yet be revealed to another. And those who have seen, have seen, yet most have only understood dimly. Therefore trust is required, and comes before understanding, for understanding can only come from Me. For I am The Only Fountain, The Only Knowledge in which is life.\n\nBeloved, when one loses sight of Me or turns away, understanding darkens. Yet one who keeps Me in front of them, coming to Me at all times and in every season, in them understanding brightens and they will have peace. For they abide in Me, and rest in the knowing that all things are held within My understanding, and are given and received according to the good pleasure of My will."},{"align":"center","text":"And indeed, this is sufficient for them.\n\n\nFor they had first sought after\n\nThe Kingdom of God and His righteousness,\n\nBy which much revelation was added to them,\n\nAccording to the Spirit which I have\n\nPoured out for them...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"mature-faith","num":25,"title":"Mature Faith","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Blessed are those who answer, “Yes, Lord,”\n\nFor their faith is revealed."},{"align":"center","text":"Blessed are those who pray, “Your will be done, Lord,”\n\nFor they have great trust."},{"align":"center","text":"Blessed are those who say, “Amen, Lord,”\n\nAt all times and in every season,\n\nFor they have understood."},{"align":"center","text":"Blessed are those who know, I AM WHO I AM;\n\nThey shall have peace...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"blessed-is-the-name-of-the-lord","num":26,"title":"Blessed Is The Name of The Lord","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"By My name is your heart sealed;\n\nFor in My name is the Spirit given,\n\nThe Spirit which also testifies of My name."},{"align":"center","text":"By My name are you established in life,\n\nAs a bride prepared for her husband."},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore, everyone who refuses\n\nTo take My name shall not see life,\n\nFor there is but One Way into life..."},{"align":"center","text":"I am The Way, says The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"sabbath-peace","num":27,"title":"Sabbath Peace","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"On the Sabbath,\n\nLet no unclean thing come from your mouth;\n\nLet only praise and beauty come forth."},{"align":"center","text":"Let My grace be your covering,\n\nLet gentleness and humility be your companion."},{"align":"center","text":"And soon you will wear a crown of glory\n\nAtop your head,\nsays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"two-robes","num":28,"title":"Two Robes","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Can one wear two robes without constraint? Or can one place one robe over another, and it not tear? Is it wise to put on one robe, while wearing another already? And shall one attempt to wear a robe of white, to conceal a soiled one beneath? Will they not both become unclean?"},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore, take off the one\n\nWhich is soiled and cast it away!\n\nThat the other may be worn properly\n\nAnd without constraint..."},{"align":"center","text":"Lest it tear, revealing your shame...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"healing-by-faith","num":29,"title":"Healing by Faith","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Faith is believing I AM WHO I AM, and that I am able to perform it. Faith can by no means be attained, nor can one grab hold of it by human means."},{"align":"justify","text":"For there are works done without faith, which are dead; and a faith which has works, which is also dead. Yet your faith came by My works, which enabled you to believe I AM WHO I AM. And all good works, which come forth from you, are My works also.\n\nTherefore if one is to be healed in accordance with My will, that same one must surrender to Me and My will, making no effort to increase their faith by human power as a means to a desired end."},{"align":"center","text":"Rather they acquiesce..."},{"align":"center","text":"Knowing that all things will be done\n\nIn their proper time and season,\n\nAccording to the love\n\nOf their Father in Heaven..."},{"align":"center","text":"Doubting nothing..."},{"align":"center","text":"Says The Lord."}]},{"id":"revelation-is-greater-than-knowledge","num":30,"title":"Revelation Is Greater Than Knowledge","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"While praying about those who have discounted The Lord’s words in The Volumes of Truth, those who think they have attained such great knowledge, The Lord spoke and said..."},{"align":"center","text":"The knowledge they possess is earthly,\n\nBut I am Heavenly!"},{"align":"center","text":"What they have received is from below,\n\nBut I am from above!"},{"align":"center","text":"All they know is passing away,\n\nYet I abide forever!"},{"align":"center","text":"They dwell in the darkness, even now,\n\nAnd remain void of understanding,\n\nYet I AM HE who dwells\n\nIn the unapproachable light!...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"the-companion-of-fools","num":31,"title":"The Companion of Fools","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Unrighteous jealousy is the companion of fools."},{"align":"center","text":"For those who envy also grab hold of jealousy,\n\nWalking hand in hand with covetousness."}]},{"id":"deliverance","num":32,"title":"Deliverance","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Blessed are those who run to Me,\n\nFor they shall be blessed in My presence."},{"align":"center","text":"Even more blessed are those\n\nWho run to Me, then obey My Word,\n\nFor their blessing is complete\n\nAnd they are at peace..."},{"align":"center","text":"Deliverance they shall surely know, says The Lord."}]},{"id":"trust-obey-and-love","num":33,"title":"Trust, Obey and Love","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Trust with abandonment,\n\nObey without expectation,\n\nAnd love without condition."},{"align":"center","text":"For in this shall you truly know Me,\n\nWith your faith progressing\n\nQuickly toward perfection...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"who-you-are","num":34,"title":"Who You Are","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Who you are at home reveals\n\nThe person you remain."},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore, do not be as the hypocrite\n\nWho has two faces, for I see all your doings,\n\nI know your heart."},{"align":"center","text":"For by a man’s actions is his heart revealed,\n\nAnd by his mouth is he defined before others...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"who-you-choose","num":35,"title":"Who You Choose","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Here is wisdom:"},{"align":"center","text":"Who you choose, not what\n\nYou choose, is the answer;\n\nFor who you choose defines what you do."},{"align":"center","text":"And whosoever chooses another,\n\nAnd not Me in truth, has chosen themselves,\n\nAnd has done according to their own will...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"embracing-the-gift","num":36,"title":"Embracing The Gift","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"The Holy Days are the\n\nStepping stones to Heaven..."},{"align":"center","text":"In understanding their meaning shall you\n\nProgress quickly along the path I have laid..."},{"align":"center","text":"And when I have fulfilled them to the last\n\nThe journey shall be complete,\n\nFor those who have accepted and received...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"notoriety","num":37,"title":"Notoriety","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Notoriety is a stumbling block at the\n\nFeet of the prideful, and fame puffs up;\n\nPride goes before a fall, and fame is short-lived;\n\nLo, a famous man is honored\n\nMore in his death than in his life."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet what does it profit?\n\nFor the meek shall inherit the earth."}]},{"id":"forbidden-fruit","num":38,"title":"Forbidden Fruit","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"If the love of money is the root of all kinds of evil,\n\nThen pride is the tree and notoriety its branches;\n\nDeath shall be the reward\n\nOf all those who eat from it..."},{"align":"center","text":"Yea darkness is reserved for all those\n\nWho take shelter in its shade."}]},{"id":"evident","num":39,"title":"Evident","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"If wisdom is justified by her children,\n\nThen the folly of fools is evident\n\nAnd the way of the wicked is death."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet the humility of the meek shall hide them\n\nIn the Day of The Lord’s Anger."}]},{"id":"the-meek-and-the-foolish","num":40,"title":"The Meek and the Foolish","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"The wise are quiet and know when to speak,\n\nAnd the humble are barely noticed."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet the prideful announce themselves as with a trumpet,\n\nAnd the plight of the slothful is made plain by their complaint."}]},{"id":"walking-in-the-word","num":41,"title":"Walking in The Word","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Rejoice in the wisdom of The Lord,\n\nAnd find joy in His correction."},{"align":"center","text":"For only those who have received\n\nOf the Spirit of Truth are able to see,\n\nAnd only those who love The Truth\n\nAre able to hear."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet only those who embrace\n\nThe Messiah fully, who also write\n\nHis words upon their hearts, will do them;\n\nAnd peace, the kind of which only The Lord\n\nCan give, shall be their companion."}]},{"id":"narrow-is-the-way","num":42,"title":"Narrow Is The Way","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Very narrow is the way, yet look how easily a little child passes through...\n\n\nMen and women of this world, you stand too tall, your girth is too wide. Lose this height therefore and bow down, for you are puffed up; as fatted cattle you have become meet for the slaughter. Therefore, refuse all this rotten food fed to the masses, and eat no more from the filthy plates served in the churches of men. Rather partake of the food I give you, and be satisfied. For I tell you the truth, until you decrease in the world’s eyes, and are humbled in your own, you shall by no means pass through. For the first harvest shall be lowly, of the lowly, says The Lord."}]},{"id":"due-reward","num":43,"title":"Due Reward","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"The high man stands proud, and the man of low degree is tread down! The eyes of The Lord have seen it, the ears of The Lord have heard it! Therefore shall the error of the proud be exposed, and the look of the lofty be brought low! For the span of My holy mountain is great, filling the breadth of the whole earth; the weight of the stone, infinite! And woe to those who are crushed beneath it! Says The Lord of Hosts."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet the man of low degree shall arise,\n\nAnd the humble sleeper shall awake from his slumber."},{"align":"center","text":"They together shall inherit the land,\n\nThey together shall live in the top of The Mountain!"},{"align":"center","text":"And the broken shall receive healing atop The Stone...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"wonderful","num":44,"title":"Wonderful","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"The power of The Lord is without end! His love covers His creation like a blanket, and the light of His glory reaches beyond the stars of heaven! His majesty is beyond comprehension; it transcends space and time! The Everlasting is His name!\n\nThe express image of The Holy is revealed, He is known of His own! His glory shines from the east even unto the west, The Sh’khinah of The Father’s only Son!\n\nWONDERFUL is His name! WONDERFUL are His ways! He wears TRUTH as a garment, and GLORY is His vesture, and LOVE is His crowning glory! All life proceeds from Him; He holds all things together by the Word of His power!"},{"align":"center","text":"His way is from everlasting,\n\nAnd with His mouth He testifies\n\nTo the Truth, always!"},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore, let us testify also;\n\nThe Father and The Son are One! ONE!...\n\n\n\nYAHUSHUA-YAHUWAH!"}]},{"id":"glad-service","num":45,"title":"Glad Service","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"A right heart brings forth glad service,\n\nAnd a joyful giver reaps what he sows;\n\nLife in abundance shall be his reward."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet the heart of the wicked seeks his own way;\n\nAnd he too shall reap according\n\nTo that which he has sown,\n\nWelcoming death when it comes."}]},{"id":"building-the-gallows","num":46,"title":"Building the Gallows","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Vanity is a rope, and pride builds the gallows;\n\nEnvy leads to hate, and jealousy\n\nBrings forth evil thoughts."},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore, beware of the thoughts of your heart,\n\nLest you follow in Haman’s error {{nav:esther:7}}\n\nAnd walk in the way of Cain, {{ref:1 John 3:12}} · {{ref:Genesis 4:8}}\n\nTo your own demise, says The Lord."}]},{"id":"walking-together-in-the-father-s-joy","num":47,"title":"Walking Together in The Father’s Joy","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Blessed is the man who gives out of the abundance of his heart. For one such as this gives, knowing in his heart that all he has is Mine and all I have is his, given and received according to the knowledge of My will for those who believe. For this man knows what it is to be My servant. He is bound by nothing, a man who walks free in all the earth, blessing the name of The Lord his God with enduring trust.\n\nTherefore those who give out of obligation know not the joy of The Lord, nor of the freedom which comes by service, helping others in My name."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet the servant whose heart leaps with joy\n\nAt the thought of washing the feet of the poor,\n\nWho also eagerly seeks out the afflicted,\n\nTo give them comfort, knows that whatsoever\n\nThey do for another they have also done for Me."},{"align":"center","text":"For these know Me, and I live in them."},{"align":"center","text":"And together we shall walk,\n\nChoosing the good and refusing the evil,\n\nUntil we walk together anew in My kingdom...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"reconciliation-in-marriage","num":48,"title":"Reconciliation in Marriage","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"An unyielding heart sows discord in marriage,\n\nAnd stubbornness shuts the door to reconciliation."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet the one who is first to say,\n\n“I’m sorry” is wise, defusing any argument;\n\nAnd the one who is quick to forgive\n\nHeals the breach."}]},{"id":"surrender","num":49,"title":"Surrender","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"The unbroken remain proud,\n\nAnd fools speak assertions\n\nWithout knowledge; they are bound."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet the one who holds their tongue is wise,\n\nAnd the one who surrenders all\n\nShall gain The Victory."}]},{"id":"ears-to-hear","num":50,"title":"Ears to Hear","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"A willing, humble heart is open to Me, and one who is deeply in love with Me will hear My voice. Yet this is not equal, nor shall every servant hear My voice in the same way.\n\nHear and understand: I have spoken to My prophets throughout the generations (for I change not), and each was given that which was required to accomplish My will among the people. Therefore rejoice, My sons and daughters, for The Most High has come down to you! And behold, I have caused My servants to hear, to receive wisdom by the power of My own spirit!"},{"align":"center","text":"Lo, by the Word of My mouth\nshall My beloved be blessed,\n\nThe prideful humbled and the haughty abased."},{"align":"center","text":"For the Word of The Lord never returns void...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"a-waving-banner","num":51,"title":"A Waving Banner","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"To the unbeliever, My Word, no matter its color or brilliance, shall be as gray clouds on a dark and dreary day. And to those pricked in their hearts, it shall be to them as an after image which ceases not from before their eyes, as a flash of lightning remains in the eyes of the one who beheld it even after they have shut their eyes to it."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet to the believer My words are cause\n\nFor celebration, a time to stop and pay attention,\n\nFor the mouth of The Living God has spoken!"},{"align":"center","text":"Both the color and brilliance they recognize,\n\nFor their eyes are wide open."},{"align":"center","text":"For them, The Source and The Author is clear,\n\nFor they see with the heart and not with the mind...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"believing-without-seeing","num":52,"title":"Believing without Seeing","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Look not outwardly for that which can only be discerned from within, and search not in the world for that which is not of this world, for I have already come... _I dwell within the hearts of men! And My spirit testifies on My behalf!_"},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore, let the hungry come to Me and eat!\n\nLet the thirsty rush to My side and drink!"},{"align":"center","text":"And let those who seek Me turn not their heads;\n\nLet them be still and listen for My voice...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord, Your Life."}]},{"id":"freedom","num":53,"title":"Freedom","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Demand nothing of Me,\n\nAnd I shall give you everything."},{"align":"center","text":"Demand everything of yourself, and I will\n\nTake it from you, and you shall be set free...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"treading-water","num":54,"title":"Treading Water","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"The servant who doubts is like a man who is tossed about on the waves of the sea. He is useless, spending all of his time trying to stay afloat, consumed with keeping his head above water."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet the man whose trust does not waver\n\nFears not the boisterous winds,\n\nNor do the billowing waves trouble him."},{"align":"center","text":"For he takes My hand, and together\nWe shall walk, upon the water...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"bearing-fruit-in-due-season","num":55,"title":"Bearing Fruit in Due Season","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Though men speak evil of you and others depart before the time, while still others question your sanity, I tell you, My words shall bear much fruit in due season. Yet the wicked will not understand, and the lukewarm will forsake them, and the worldly will seek to bind them and place them in a corner."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet those who are wise will understand,\n\nAnd in them shall a flame arise,\n\nIn them shall My words be written;\n\nBehold, they shall bear fruit\n\nIn accordance with My likeness!"},{"align":"center","text":"For they were bound to Me from\n\nThe beginning, and did not waver...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord your Redeemer."}]},{"id":"the-devoted-servant","num":56,"title":"The Devoted Servant","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"What is the least thing done in service toward Me,\nCompared with that which My servant\n\nWishes to do most for himself?\n\n\n\nYet the servant who is truly devoted\n\nTo Me puts no difference between them;\n\nIn his eyes they are one and the same;\n\nIn his heart the former fulfills the latter.\n\n\n\nFor have I not said,\n“A right heart brings forth glad service”?...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"impaired-vision","num":57,"title":"Impaired Vision","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"I saw a star fall from Heaven, while the sons of men laughed. For they have no vision, neither are they able to see beyond that which is in front of them. And even this they deny, for they love deception and the truth is not at all convenient."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet the sons of God hold their tongues,\n\nAnd open not their mouths."},{"align":"center","text":"As tears run down their faces,\n\nThey look upon creation with new eyes\n\nAnd restored vision, embracing The Promise,\n\nAbiding in The Hope of Salvation...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-holy-flame","num":58,"title":"The Holy Flame","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Hear and seek to understand: The Word of God is fire, each word a burning flame in the midst of an immense fire. The countenance of The Lord is a fire, and a flame within a fire. The glory of The Lord is perfect, a pure light, a flame within a flame, a fire engulfing all creation!\n\nYAHUWAH is One, and His name, One; His name is in Him and is Him. YAHUWAH is His name, and His name is One with Him. They are not separate, but one, even as The Father and The Son are One - a flame within a flame, within an immense fire.\n\nYAHUWAH has no beginning and no end, even as His name. Therefore nothing is outside YAHUWAH, for His being is infinite. And those who pass outside creation enter into His eternal glory, or are burned up in His devouring fire, in His everlasting flame.\n\nTherefore no one may come to The Father except through The Son, YAHUSHUA, The Purifying Flame. For only The Holy Flame may dwell within The Fire, for YAH is holy. And all those void of The Flame will consume away; they shall cease to exist. For ALL must pass through the fire, ALL are subject to the power of The Flame - the wicked purged, and the penitent purified."}]},{"id":"more","num":59,"title":"More","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"I have seen the sun rise upon the mountains of Israel, I have seen the light of the moon illuminate the valleys of Judah, I have even seen the stars fall from the heavens! Yet never have I seen a wonder such as this, never have I beheld such a wondrous thing!\n\nI have seen a brilliant light, a perfect likeness! Behold, I have stepped into the fire! Yet instead of burning, I received understanding; and in place of my wounds, I received healing in this flame!\n\nWhat a wondrous and beautiful place! Such overwhelming, pure love in the light of His glory, consuming me where I stand, strengthening me as I fall down, my tears flowing as my life departs from me! Yet I do not die. Rather the presence of The Lord of Hosts rises up in me!\n\nIs this Heaven? Yes! It is The Kingdom! For before me is the likeness of a Man, bright and shining! He is beckoning me! I see the holes in His hands and in His feet, as I am pulled toward His open arms!"},{"align":"center","text":"I am losing myself,\n\nYet I feel as though I am being born!\n\nI was dead, and now I am alive again,\n\nThe man I was passing away as His life rushes in!"},{"align":"center","text":"And what more can I say?\n\nWhat more shall I ask of Him?..."},{"align":"center","text":"Only this: MORE!"}]},{"id":"the-selfless-servant","num":60,"title":"The Selfless Servant","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"The selfless servant shall be filled and put to use in all the earth, dwelling always in the inner courts of My love, where grace and truth flow as a river which never runs dry, partaking of My glory, bearing fruit in kind. For he who dwells in the secret place of The Most High abides in the shadow of The Almighty, and from this servant nothing is withheld.\n\nLo, within him are written The Commandments of God, and engraven upon his heart is the name of love and pure righteousness. In his mind’s eye he sees the holy sacrifice, the salvation of many. With his lips he sings the song of The Lamb, and with his mouth he testifies to the glory of The Lord, without ceasing.\n\n\nFor great is YAHUWAH his God, and holy is The One who is poured out! For the mouths of the pure in heart are open, and He shall surely fill them up, even as a welcomed rain in the height of summer, says The Lord."}]},{"id":"made-whole","num":61,"title":"Made Whole","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"This is wisdom: I AM HE!"},{"align":"center","text":"And this is understanding:\n\nI abide forever! All healing is in Me!"},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore everyone who comes to Me is made whole,\n\nAnd everyone who lives in Me shall abide forever...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"eternal-fire","num":62,"title":"Eternal Fire","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"The Lord our God has kindled a fire;\n\nHis heart is set ablaze over His beloved!\n\n\n\nThus all who willingly pass through\n\nThe Flame shall be purified,\n\nRefined and restored in the image\n\nIn which He created them."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet the wicked shall never be established;\n\nTheir places shall be removed,\n\nBurned up, utterly consumed!"},{"align":"center","text":"For The Lord our God is a consuming fire,\n\nThe Purifying Flame!"}]},{"id":"the-sower-and-the-reaper","num":63,"title":"The Sower and The Reaper","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Such troubled children, always divided. None have learned to walk, not one truly knows Me. Yea, darkness is overhead, and many have fallen back to sleep. In the height of summer they withered, under the heat of the noonday sun they became faint and fell down. And now the time of the harvest is here, relief is very near, yet who opens their eyes to look upon Me?"},{"align":"center","text":"Who stands up and bears their burden gladly?..."},{"align":"center","text":"That all might eat and rejoice in their labors,\n\nThat all might rejoice and give thanks together\n\nFor the bounty which I have provided..."},{"align":"center","text":"Looking to the day when the plowman overtakes the reaper,\n\nAnd the treader of grapes Him who sows seed... {{ref:Amos 9:13}}\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-salvation-day","num":64,"title":"The Salvation Day","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"The Salvation Day of Men is four-fold:"},{"align":"center","text":"It was ordained before the foundation\n\nOf the world, fulfilled at My birth,\n\nFinished at My death on the cross,\n\nAnd solidified eternally upon My resurrection...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"the-truth-endures-forever","num":65,"title":"The Truth Endures Forever","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"The power of a lie is only as strong as those who believe it;\n\nYet The Truth will set you free."},{"align":"center","text":"All lies are born of the evil one and shall perish;\n\nYet The Truth endures forever."}]},{"id":"anathema","num":66,"title":"Anathema","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"_Thus says The Lord:_ As it is written, My people are destroyed for lack of knowledge! And because they have rejected knowledge, I must also reject them! {{ref:Hosea 4:6}}_... In all their forsaking of Me are they taken away! On account of their pride they reject Me, and in their arrogance do they hold fast to their own way, treading the wide path! Therefore are the walls of Jerusalem broken down! Thus is the vineyard of The Lord tread down! Behold, the vats overflow, every vessel is tipped, all new wine evaporates in the fire! And still, My people are not saved!_"}]},{"id":"the-redeemer","num":67,"title":"The Redeemer","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Behold, I had come,\n\nThe Son who was completely blameless,\n\nTo bear the guilt of all The Father’s children..."},{"align":"center","text":"The Just for the unjust;\n\nThe Innocent for the guilty;\n\nThe Son of Man for the sons of men...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"letting-go","num":68,"title":"Letting Go","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Here is wisdom:"},{"align":"center","text":"For one to depart this world\n\nThey must first depart in spirit,\n\nWillingly forsaking their life in this world,\n\nFully embracing Mine..."},{"align":"center","text":"Coming to Me free,\n\nWithout any form of malice\n\nIn their heart toward another..."},{"align":"center","text":"Then shall they be taken, says The Lord."}]},{"id":"true-fellowship","num":69,"title":"True Fellowship","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"True fellowship comes not by words\n\nSpoken amongst a group of united people."},{"align":"center","text":"Rather it starts with the heart,\n\nAnd is found in the stillness of My spirit,\n\nWhere My peace mends the broken\n\nAnd My gentle caress gladdens the heart."},{"align":"center","text":"For all those found at the feet of The Lord\n\nAre covered with grace,\n\nAnd those who abide in My love\n\nAre indeed of one accord...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"walk-humbly-with-your-god","num":70,"title":"Walk Humbly with Your God","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Hear and understand: The moment pride enters a man, and the moment he stands in front of Me to look elsewhere, is the same moment My hand is removed. For I have shown you, My servants, what is good and that which I require: _That you should do justly, love mercy, and walk humbly with your God. {{ref:Micah 6:8}}_"},{"align":"center","text":"Yet how can one behold My face while\n\nLooking elsewhere, seeking glory for themselves?"},{"align":"center","text":"And how can one who has stepped\n\nIn front of Me walk in My footsteps?"},{"align":"center","text":"Beloved, how shall one who runs away from Me,\n\nTo tread another path, take My hand?...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"faith","num":71,"title":"Faith","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"When My servant no longer seeks to see with his eyes, nor hear with his ears, the fulfillment of those things written, then he will know his faith is near to completion, says The Lord. For one who must see with his eyes lacks trust, and one who has itching ears lacks understanding."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet the servant who truly believes is no longer\nBound by the need for confirmation;\n\nHe seeks not after signs, nor does\n\nHe sit idle waiting for the news."},{"align":"center","text":"For his trust is complete, his understanding full,\n\nAnd he is at peace, walking in the ways of The Lord."}]},{"id":"walking-free","num":72,"title":"Walking Free","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"One who bears their own burdens\n\nMust also bear the heat of the day."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet one who lets go, cutting every cord that\n\nBinds them to this world, walks free,\n\nAnd shall be given eagle’s wings...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"antidote","num":73,"title":"Antidote","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Judging another man’s servant poisons the heart\n\nAnd corrupts every good intention."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet judging one’s own judgment,\n\nTaking every thought captive,\n\nRenders this poison neutral and of no effect...\n\n\nRighteous discernment according to\n\nThat which the Spirit reveals, says The Lord."}]},{"id":"idle-hands","num":74,"title":"Idle Hands","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Idle hands lack bread, and an idle heart lacks trust;\n\nTheir backs are bent down always, their countenances fallen,\n\nTheir eyelids have grown very heavy."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet love strengthens the spirit, and washing another’s feet\n\nIs good for the soul, renewing the whole of the body...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"i-remain-always","num":75,"title":"I Remain Always","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"I remain always The Good Teacher,\n\nWho continually reminds His students\n\nOf that which He has taught them\n\nBefore they lose sight of The Goal."},{"align":"center","text":"I remain also The Faithful Shepherd,\n\nWho calls to His sheep before they\n\nHave wandered too far..."},{"align":"center","text":"The Wise and Loving Father,\n\nWho makes the sins of His beloved\n\nKnown early, while they are still able\n\nTo step easily off the crooked path...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"elect-and-precious","num":76,"title":"Elect and Precious","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"You are more than the filth that covers you,\n\nMore than the sin that fills you,\n\nMuch more than the choices you make;\n\nFor I see your beauty, I know your heart\n\nAnd the love which you have for Me.\n\n\n\nBehold, I know you as you are and will be, with Me where I am.\n\n\n\nYou are not that which you choose in a moment of weakness;\n\nYou are that which I have created, and will become\n\nThat which I restore, and will remain always\n\nA beautiful, finished work, elect and precious,\n\nMy everlasting treasure, even as I shall be yours also.\n\n\n\nFor I know My own, says The Lord."}]},{"id":"grace-and-the-moral-law","num":77,"title":"Grace AND The Moral Law","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Hear and understand: Salvation can in no wise depart from you, once received. Therefore, seek to please The Father AND keep The Law.\n\nFor how can one who walks in Me by grace also walk in that which had condemned them? Shall My people reach toward Heaven with their hands, while their feet continue to tread the wide path which leads to destruction? And how shall one who loves Me take My hand and walk beside Me, with one foot on the good ground and the other in the grave?\n\nTherefore knowledge must increase, and sin decrease, to enter The Kingdom of Heaven. For one who is under grace bears fruit of the same; and The One who kept The Law of The Father revealed that grace by works."},{"align":"center","text":"So then, Grace is first and everlasting."},{"align":"center","text":"Then comes works, the first works done in faith,\n\nEven the first fruits bore in your lives..."},{"align":"center","text":"Which is to love The Father and one another,\n\nBy keeping The Law, says The Lord."}]},{"id":"a-desirable-union","num":78,"title":"A Desirable Union","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"_Thus says The Lord to those who seek Him:_ Do you abide in Me? Have you received of that which I offer? For until one has stilled their heart and quieted the thoughts of their mind, they shall by no means hear that which the Spirit speaks. How then shall they walk in My will, if they are unable to discern?\n\nYet everyone who looks for Me, with all their heart and with all their soul, shall surely find Me! And everyone who seeks My will, in all trust, shall know it! And in the secret place of My presence shall we break bread together, set apart from the many plots of the evil one, away from the noise of this world."},{"align":"center","text":"For this is where quiet understanding abounds\n\nAnd the will of The Lord is made plain..."},{"align":"center","text":"Where the broken receive peace and every\n\nSin is absolved in My healing embrace;\n\nWhere the heart of every son rests\n\nSecurely in the hands of his Father,\n\nAnd where the hearts of My daughters are\n\nRestored and shine anew in My likeness..."},{"align":"center","text":"A desirable union, fulfilling every desire\n\nOf the heart in My love, says The Lord."}]},{"id":"consider-my-love","num":79,"title":"Consider My Love","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Behold My hands and My feet, and consider My love;\n\nFor the scars of My passion remain,\n\nA holy, everlasting covenant\n\nWritten in the blood of The Lamb."},{"align":"center","text":"Taste and see, beloved, drink!\n\nUntil that which is veiled is veiled no longer,\n\nUntil the void within your heart is filled."},{"align":"center","text":"For My love was written in every stripe I endured for you,\n\nPoured out in every drop of blood I shed for you,\n\nRevealed when you pierced My hands and My feet."},{"align":"center","text":"Beloved, I am married unto you!..."},{"align":"center","text":"A union sealed forever in the blood we share...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"a-man-of-god","num":80,"title":"A Man of God","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"A man of God is humble and quiet\n\nUntil called upon to speak,\n\nA man of low degree who treads softly\n\nUntil called upon to act..."},{"align":"center","text":"A lowly man who is completely in love with Me,\n\nWho does not his own will nor seek his own way..."},{"align":"center","text":"A man who waits upon The Lord,\n\nAnd hesitates not when the command\n\nComes down from the mouth of The Lord his God..."},{"align":"center","text":"A man after My own heart, My servant, My friend...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-reward","num":81,"title":"The Reward","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"He who trusts in The Lord shall receive healing wings and soar high above the storm! At the call of The Most High, he shall ascend the heights of the heavens with The Lord beside him! Yea, Beauty shall be his dwelling place, and in the sanctuary of God’s mercy shall he worship He who sits on the throne! In one accord and with one spirit shall all praise The God of Jacob, sharing in the depths of Mashiach, as love flows from one heart to another! For YAHUWAH is God alone, He who laid the foundations of the earth, The One who is and was and is to come, The Almighty! YAHUSHUA-YAHUWAH!"},{"align":"center","text":"Blessed, therefore, are all those who escape!"},{"align":"center","text":"For they have called upon the name\n\nOf The Lord, in sincerity and in truth,\n\nAnd have given up everything to follow Him."},{"align":"center","text":"Indeed, they have received their reward."}]},{"id":"love-has-saved-them","num":82,"title":"Love Has Saved Them","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Those who were full shall be left empty,\n\nSo they may be truly filled up, and those\n\nWho were thought of as first shall be last."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet those who were forsaken as last\n\nShall be first partakers of The Glory.\n\n\n\n\nAnd those without knowledge shall be given\n\nGreat knowledge, for Love has saved them."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet those who had attained great knowledge\n\nShall be brought down to shame, so they too\n\nMay be glorified in My presence,\n\nFor Love has saved them...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"offering-a-gift","num":83,"title":"Offering a Gift","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"A gift demanded is no gift at all;\n\nAnd anyone forced to receive a gift\n\nNever truly receives it."},{"align":"center","text":"Thus when offering a gift,\n\nOne does not demand its acceptance,\n\nLest the gift be polluted and a division occur,\n\nCausing both to depart offended...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"accepting-the-gift","num":84,"title":"Accepting The Gift","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"What is life without love?\n\nAnd what is love without the\n\nFree will to choose love?"},{"align":"center","text":"I tell you the truth,\n\nA gift commanded is no gift at all!"},{"align":"center","text":"Yet a gift accepted is where you\n\nShall find life, love and salvation...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"who-do-you-serve","num":85,"title":"Who Do You Serve?","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"No servant is greater than his master..."},{"align":"center","text":"How he serves others shows the master he serves;\n\nHow he serves his master reveals the master within him;\n\nAnd what the master suffers will his servant suffer also,\n\nFor he serves in his name.\n\n\n\n\nNo one can serve two masters..."},{"align":"center","text":"Either he will hate the one and love the other,\n\nOr he will be devoted to the one and despise the other {{ref:Matthew 6:24}}...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"embracing-the-call-of-the-lord","num":86,"title":"Embracing the Call of The Lord","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"There is no greater love than to lay down your life for another, and blessed is the one who embraces the calling of The Lord wholeheartedly. For a servant such as this lays down his life each day, bearing his cross after Me. Upon waking he kneels down at the feet of The Lord, with an open heart and open hands. And in this servant My soul delights.\n\nFor the servants of The Most High uphold My cause. And as My love is poured out, it fills the hearts of the penitent, even as My stern correction and harsh discipline comes swiftly upon the defiant. For My ways are not human ways. For I do what is right by My children, doing that which is most needful for each one, that they may come to Me in their due season. I AM THE LORD."}]},{"id":"blowing-the-trumpet","num":87,"title":"Blowing The Trumpet","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"My servants, to warn your brothers and sisters,\n\nEven to your neighbors and countrymen,\n\nWhether they will hear or whether\n\nThey will forbear, is LOVE."},{"align":"center","text":"For only an evil man would fail to warn his fellows,\n\nWhen he had knowledge of coming calamity."},{"align":"center","text":"And only a wicked man meet for death would save himself,\n\nWhile forsaking those nearby to the sword...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"a-pillar-of-strength","num":88,"title":"A Pillar of Strength","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"My forgiveness runs far and wide, entering deep into the hearts of those who come to Me in sincere repentance. Yet many of My sheep believe themselves to be above reproach, and in this do they greatly err. Therefore let all My beloved grow wise in Me, and learn also to walk in My ways. For I am a pillar of strength to those of low degree! I uphold the powerless and steady the weary, as I renew the hearts of My elect!"},{"align":"center","text":"Behold, I fill all those who come to Me empty with\n\nSpirit and grace, as they walk with Me into everlasting life!\n\nIndeed, they shall experience life in abundance, forevermore!..."},{"align":"center","text":"Life of such a kind, which is only found in Me and I am...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"without-condition","num":89,"title":"Without Condition","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Learn the lesson of obedience in The Lord."},{"align":"center","text":"For obedience is far greater than\n\nWitnessing a prophecy come to pass,\n\nAnd much greater than receiving healing\n\nBy a miracle, for obedience is born of love."},{"align":"center","text":"For those who have no trust seek after signs,\n\nAnd those who remain in unbelief wait for miracles."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet only those who love Me, without condition,\n\nWill remain faithful, and only those who truly\n\nKnow Me will endure in times of trouble...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"rejoicing-over-my-sons-and-daughters","num":90,"title":"Rejoicing Over My Sons and Daughters","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"My glory is revealed in the lives of all My children, no matter what path they had chosen, no matter how they have tread. I know My own, and I know when each will come to Me and how each shall come to walk in Me. And by this I am glorified, even as each shall also share in My glory.\n\nFor to one, it is as the son who remained faithful to his father, and never lost his inheritance, but kept it close his whole life. Yet to the other, it is as the prodigal son {{ref:Luke 15:11-32}} who went out and wasted his inheritance in the world, yet was met with much rejoicing when he returned home. For the one who was faithful remained in his father’s love, and was rejoiced over his whole life; and the other returned to his father’s love, and was met with much rejoicing. Yet both shall dwell in the house of their Father together, from that day onward, sharing equally in all he had laid up in store for them, forever."},{"align":"center","text":"Thus by one I am glorified in their walk,\n\nAnd by another in their return.\n\n\n\nI AM THE LORD."}]},{"id":"pure-love","num":91,"title":"Pure Love","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"The love of man is born from the desires of the flesh and comes forth from a place of longing, to fill a void which remains empty; affections built upon conditions and unrealistic expectations, learned in a world without natural affection - corrupt.\n\nYet My love is a light which shines in a dark place, warmth which brings peace and healing to those whose hearts have grown cold; a cup overflowing, never-ending, affection in its purest form - unconditional."},{"align":"justify","text":"Therefore come to Me, beloved, that our hearts may be satisfied! For all those who sincerely long for Me shall surely receive of Me, and all those who obey My voice shall surely walk beside Me, and all those who love Me, above all else, shall know the depths of My Mercy. For I shall take them, and they shall dwell with Me, where I am, in The Kingdom of My joy, forever... Says The Lord."}]},{"id":"trust-in-the-holy-one","num":92,"title":"Trust in The Holy One","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"The presence of The Almighty is a consuming fire, a purifying flame. The cloud of The Almighty is a covering for all who put their trust in Him. The Sanctuary of His peace is in His Holy One, and none shall fear who abide in Him. And though the terror of The Lord comes upon all nations, it shall not approach the penitent, nor shall the trembling of the humble continue without comfort. For The Lord God has a Holy One, and in Him is the loving mercy of God revealed. In His bosom are healing tears and laughter, joy beyond compare, the fullness of love, life without end."},{"align":"center","text":"Behold, The Lord has come down to look upon\n\nThe rage of the nations, to search the hearts of men...\n\n\n\nThe Mighty One has come down to gather His own,\n\nTo take from among them the penitent,\n\nEveryone of a contrite heart and humble spirit...\n\n\nThose who do justly and love mercy,\n\nWhose eyes long to look upon their King...\n\n\nThose whose hands reach out for His healing touch,\n\nWhose fingers know His wounds,\n\nWhose lips have tasted of the divine gift,\n\nDrinking from His cup, always."}]},{"id":"choose-me","num":93,"title":"Choose Me","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Behold, The Gift is given already!"},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore, all those who come to Me, who love Me\n\nWith all their heart, with all their mind, with all their soul\n\nAnd with all their strength, shall be blessed indeed!"},{"align":"center","text":"For is it not written:\n\n\"Wisdom is justified by her children\"? {{ref:Luke 7:35}}"},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore, here is wisdom: CHOOSE ME!...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"trust-in-me","num":94,"title":"Trust in Me","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"I am The First! Behold, I am also The Last!"},{"align":"center","text":"Blessed therefore are all those who bow down before Me;\n\nFor in them shall the vision be made complete\n\nAnd The Word established, even as it was\n\nAt the first and shall also be at the last."},{"align":"center","text":"Trust in Me therefore, for I AM HE!...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"breaking-through-the-barriers","num":95,"title":"Breaking Through the Barriers","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"_Thus says The Lord:_ When tears well up, let them burst forth as a flood overflowing the dam; let them break through the barriers!\n\n\nYet understand this: Let not your tears turn to anger when shed over hurt, nor let resentment come forth, lest you strengthen the dam and build up the barriers, leading to rebellion against The Lord as you hold unforgiveness in your heart. Beloved, let your tears flow when the Spirit convicts you! Let them cleanse your eyes so you may see, as your heart is set free! And no more resist the cleansing of The Lord."}]},{"id":"whose-robes-do-you-wear","num":96,"title":"Whose Robes Do You Wear?","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Pay attention to the robes you wear,\n\nAnd those which you seek to put on."},{"align":"center","text":"Rather be willing to come to The Lord naked,\n\nThat He may clothe you with that\n\nWhich He has prepared for you."}]},{"id":"treat-everyday-as-the-sabbath","num":97,"title":"Treat Everyday as The Sabbath","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Why do you depart from the Sabbath at sundown\n\nAnd return to the ways of the world, welcoming in again\n\nThat which you shut the door to on the Sabbath?"},{"align":"center","text":"Rather treat everyday as the Sabbath, and you will do well...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"the-sound-of-my-love","num":98,"title":"The Sound of My Love","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"I have laid My heart open before your eyes,\n\nAnd into your ears I have spoken."},{"align":"center","text":"As a harpist playing soft music, beautiful music,\n\nPlucking each string with delicate fingers,\n\nI revealed the song of My heart to you."},{"align":"center","text":"With precise strokes, in gentle tones of healing,\n\nWith many notes of unending love\n\nAnd by soothing vibrations of peace,\n\nDid the sound of My love speak."},{"align":"center","text":"And I, even I, The Lord of Hosts, did not withhold from you...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"eternity-with-the-lord","num":99,"title":"Eternity with The Lord","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Who are these I have made? And what man have I brought forth from the dust of the earth, that I might share My glory with him? There are none worthy; not one formed from the dust of the earth who knows Me; not one who is righteous, no, not one. All lie down in death, all return to the dust of the earth.\n\n\n_Yet I came down to you in the image in which I formed you, so you might receive of Me and have life, that you might share in My wisdom and find healing, great peace in My love... Exchanging your life for Mine...\n\nThat you might roam free in My creation, close to Me, at My side always, until your first days are called ancient and your latter days laughter... Years beyond number...\n\nThousands of years passing as the setting of the sun, millions of days passing by as a breeze caressing the face of the forever young... Each one remembered as yesterday, says The Lord YahuShua._"}]},{"id":"drink-deeply-from-this-vine","num":100,"title":"Drink Deeply from This Vine","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"My children, seek My glory and look to My Righteousness, for The Kingdom of Heaven is at hand! Look into My eyes, open your ears to My voice, for the mouth of The Lord has spoken! Return to the first works; it is time to be consumed in your First Love!"},{"align":"center","text":"Beloved, see the Word of The Lord,\n\nDrink deeply from this vine!"},{"align":"center","text":"Consider My Mercy and the name of Love,\n\nThat you may know Me as I truly am,\n\nThat we may be one!"},{"align":"center","text":"Consider, for it is time, says The Lord."}]},{"id":"a-sure-way","num":101,"title":"A Sure Way","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"My words are pure,\n\nA solid foundation beneath the feet\n\nOf My beloved, a sure way for all who believe."},{"align":"center","text":"My words are a strong staff in the hand\n\nOf all those who do them, and all who place\n\nTheir trust in Me will never falter...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"envy","num":102,"title":"Envy","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Envy is a double-ended sword. One end is covetousness, piercing the heart of those who envy; the other is pride, piercing the heart of those being envied. Behold, envy is also a snare. For those who envy are held captive by covetousness, and those who are envied are easily ensnared by pride."},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore repent, and place\n\nAll your trust in The Messiah."},{"align":"center","text":"Make Him your focus,\n\nYour only desire, and He will keep\n\nYour foot from being taken."},{"align":"center","text":"Indeed, He will preserve your life."}]},{"id":"the-feasts-of-the-lord","num":103,"title":"The Feasts of The Lord","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"In these Seven is wisdom and understanding, the very mind of God. For the Holy Days are revelation, revealing hidden things kept secret since the world began - signposts of things to come, a foretaste of The Kingdom, a glimpse into the Glory of God even as the Scriptures, unfolding and coming to light as the will of God is manifest, says The Lord."},{"align":"center","text":"Behold, four are fulfilled:\n\nSalvation assured, sin and death overcome, the Spirit given.\n\n\n\nThree are coming quickly:\n\nSin destroyed, evil bound, My seat taken, Judgment...\n\n\n\nA new day, even one thousand years...\n\n\n\nThen a short season, Consummation...\n\n\n\nAn everlasting day in The Lord!"}]},{"id":"beyond-question","num":104,"title":"Beyond Question","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"The Lord is eternal; HE IS! He never ends! His love, His mercy, His justice, His majesty, His glory, His sorrow, all that He is endures forever!\n\nLikewise His creation has no end, no boundaries! There are no limits to contain it, for it is as He is! HE IS THE CREATOR! - Everlasting, eternal, The Alpha and Omega, The Beginning and The End, The First and The Last by whom all things exist and have their being, through whom all living things have life!\n\nKiss The Son, therefore! Bow down heavily and give Him glory! Let the knowledge of who He is fill your heart with wonder and awe, with great reverence and worship! Give Him thanks and praise! For Holy is The Lord God Almighty, His ways past finding out! For who can understand the knowledge of The Lord contained within creation, or know the depths of His wisdom?! Yet His Glory surrounds us on every side, testifying to His majesty beyond question! Indeed, we are without excuse!"},{"align":"center","text":"Behold, even the whole of creation shouts,\n\n“YAHUSHUA is YAHUWAH!”"},{"align":"center","text":"For it is He by whom all things consist,\n\nIt is He who causes to be!\n\nFor The Lord our God is One!"}]},{"id":"the-song-of-the-lamb","num":105,"title":"The Song of The Lamb","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Eat of Me, partake of My words, and be filled! Breathe Me in, that the song of The Lamb may dwell within you! For it is the knowledge of My love, the revelation of who I truly am! - A song, a chorus, soon to be a symphony, a great outpouring of revelation to the praise of My glory!"},{"align":"center","text":"Beloved, it is also the music we share,\n\nSweet melodies of grace and peace\n\nPlaying softly within your heart,\n\nEach string plucked gently and surely..."},{"align":"center","text":"The sound of My love revealed\n\nIn you and through you..."},{"align":"center","text":"My spirit, My breath,\n\nMy life given and received,\n\nBearing much fruit in The Beloved...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"a-sure-foundation","num":106,"title":"A Sure Foundation","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Old houses stand upon old foundations,\n\nAnd new houses upon new foundations;\n\nA new house cannot be built atop another,\n\nNor does one build a new house\n\nUpon an old foundation."},{"align":"center","text":"No, the old house must be torn down\n\nAnd the old foundation removed,\n\nMaking room for the new foundation\n\nTo be poured, that the new house\n\nMay rest securely upon it..."},{"align":"center","text":"Behold the house!\n\nA house with a sure foundation, a house able\n\nTo withstand even the strongest of storms...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"integrity","num":107,"title":"Integrity","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Obedience is more than trust,\n\nAnd trust much more than obedience."},{"align":"center","text":"For obedience by itself\n\nBears bitter fruit in the end,\n\nAnd trust left alone becomes a lie...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"remembering-the-ascension-looking-to-the-blessed-hope","num":108,"title":"Remembering the Ascension, Looking to the Blessed Hope","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"That which was bitter shall be made sweet, and that which brought tears of sadness shall be turned to great rejoicing. For indeed The Bridegroom was taken from them, and has been a long time in coming. Yet those who have waited with all eagerness shall have their hope realized, and those who watched with steadfast trust shall not be put to shame; neither shall those who have fallen asleep be disappointed."},{"align":"center","text":"For the Bride shall have her heart’s desire,\n\nAnd My prophets their due reward."},{"align":"center","text":"For all those who belong to Me have tasted,\n\nAnd behold, My prophets have surely seen...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-justice-of-god","num":109,"title":"The Justice of God","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"The justice of God rests atop the mountain, and comes forth with a great noise! The retribution of The Lord rains down upon the mountains and gathers strength! It rushes down the steep places, catching many unawares! It gathers together and rages through the valleys, leaping over the banks, breaking down the walls, destroying every barrier! A terrible deluge!\n\nBehold, the trees are fallen and torn from their places, their branches broken and mangled, their roots laid bare! Unrecognizable!"},{"align":"center","text":"Thus is the wrath of God,\n\nThus is the Day of The Lord’s Anger:"},{"align":"center","text":"Destruction in a moment, a tearing down,\n\nA wiping away, a great threshing,\n\nA carrying away of all that offends!..."},{"align":"center","text":"Until all that is hidden is exposed,\n\nAnd that which is high and lofty\n\nIs brought low..."},{"align":"center","text":"Until every fruitful hill is made barren,\n\nAnd every lush valley is stripped\n\nAnd bares neither leaf nor fruit…"},{"align":"center","text":"Darkness, thick clouds and darkness..."},{"align":"center","text":"The shadow of death."}]},{"id":"providence","num":110,"title":"Providence","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"My people are a strange and peculiar people. Indeed, they are accounted by the multitude as those who are of unsound mind. Yet My servants are men of action, men with strong trust, men of clout in The Lord; men who are unwavering in My purpose who also care for those given them, willing to go wheresoever I send them, unafraid to do whatever is needful.\n\nYet the plight of the slothful shall be filled with troubles, as the sun sets upon their need. For in their listlessness they were unaware and did not seek after My will, to know it, nor have they risen up to walk in that which I have spoken already. Thus providence is drawn back, until the sluggard has no place.\n\n\nHave I not spoken to these things already, in many Letters? Have I not revealed My will and that in which I am most pleased, by My many words? And still My people draw back from My voice and My servants sit idle and fold the hands, closing their eyes to their need while forsaking those placed under their care, both those near to them and those afar off, says The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-true-church","num":111,"title":"The True Church","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"I am The Church - Its walls, its pews,\n\nIts pulpit, its altar, its very foundation."},{"align":"center","text":"When sitting in My church, you can behold Heaven;\n\nThere is no ceiling to keep you from enlightenment."},{"align":"center","text":"And if I am your sanctuary, your four walls of faith,\n\nYour resting place of worship, The Word and the Spirit,\n\nThe Stone upon which all must be broken,\n\nThe Very Cornerstone of Life,\n\nThen Heaven is open before the eyes of all\n\nWho dwell in Me and become My body...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"charity","num":112,"title":"Charity","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Comfort the sick, lift up the downtrodden, and visit those in prison; clothe the naked, shelter the homeless, and above all feed the hungry; do so in My name. For in Me shall all find comfort, exaltation, companionship, warm coverings and sanctuary from the storm; even food and drink for their soul shall they receive in Me. For all these things are the very definition and purpose of love."},{"align":"center","text":"Thus as I am, so also were you created..."},{"align":"center","text":"Understand Love."},{"align":"center","text":"For in My love were you created,\n\nTo receive and to give;\n\nAnd in the giving does one also receive."},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore, love one another\n\nAs I have loved you,\n\nSays The Lord your Redeemer."}]},{"id":"without-hesitation","num":113,"title":"Without Hesitation","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Blessed are My servants who seek to\n\nObey My commands without hesitation,\n\nFor their trust is apparent;\n\nBlessed are those who seek to please Me,\n\nFor in them am I well pleased."},{"align":"center","text":"For no man can step forward without trust,\n\nAnd one who is void of belief is\n\nConsumed by doubt and fear.\n\nAnd I have already told you that pride blinds\n\nThe eyes and arrogance stops the ears."},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore let My servants step\n\nForward without hesitation, and ask,\n\nThat their blessing may be compounded\n\nAnd their belief increased!...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"steadfast-faith","num":114,"title":"Steadfast Faith","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Blessed is the wise and faithful servant,\n\nWho gives no thought to how they are\n\nPerceived in the eyes of others."},{"align":"center","text":"For they obey My voice,\n\nAnd are not dismayed by the looks\n\nOf those who judge without knowledge."},{"align":"center","text":"Indeed, they seek only to please their Master,\n\nHaving no need of the approval of others...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"perseverance","num":115,"title":"Perseverance","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"There can be no birth apart from travail,\n\nFor birth is always accompanied\n\nBy much travail."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet oh how blessed are those\n\nWho persevere with their hearts\n\nFixed upon the goal, enduring the pain,\n\nFor they shall surely receive their reward...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"one-body","num":116,"title":"One Body","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"This is the way of The Lord..."},{"align":"center","text":"That one in need in My body\n\nBe supported by their brothers and sisters,\n\nWith all members becoming one..."},{"align":"center","text":"One body, in Me..."},{"align":"center","text":"That he who is able to walk in Me\n\nDwell alongside those who are weak,\n\nFor they are in need of strengthening..."},{"align":"center","text":"Lo, you shall all wash each other’s feet!..."},{"align":"center","text":"Even as I do likewise\n\nThrough you and amongst you,\n\nTo the praise of My glory...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"devotion","num":117,"title":"Devotion","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Of My servants I require obedience, with all trust,\n\nPure service in The Lord..."},{"align":"center","text":"An eager servant willing to obey without hesitation,\n\nEven when they lack understanding;\n\nA humble servant who remains in My love,\n\nA disciple who has breathed Me in..."},{"align":"center","text":"A devoted son or daughter who loves Me more than these...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"unrestrained","num":118,"title":"Unrestrained","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Consider this, says The Lord; ponder it and also receive it: By good works you will not find Me, yet good works are found in Me. And by My works shall you begin to know Me, for My works shall be done in you.\n\n\nYet understand this also: Where human power is, pride follows close behind. Yet one who surrenders to The Lord will be given eagle’s wings. Yea nothing shall be impossible for them, for I shall be with them and in them, says The Lord.\n\nIn that day, wheresoever I am will My servants be also, and wheresoever I go My servants will follow. And whatsoever I decree will be done in an instant, and those who are chosen will go for Me without hesitation, and that which I speak in this place will be heard in another. And no more shall My servants be restrained, by any means! Declares The Lord. For it is I, The King of Glory, who has spoken it."}]},{"id":"blurred-vision","num":119,"title":"Blurred Vision","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"One who answers a matter in the name of The Lord, while being ignorant or unsure, is foolish. And one who judges a matter without knowledge leans upon pride, wearing pretense as a garment.\n\nThus the one who steps in front of Me shall surely stumble, and the one who seats himself upon My throne shall be cast down. For pride does indeed come before the fall, and those who judge without knowledge shall be made to sit upon the ground. I AM THE LORD."}]},{"id":"responsibility","num":120,"title":"Responsibility","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"One who does not take responsibility\n\nFor their wrong-doings can by\n\nNo means place them at My feet;\n\nAnd until one faces their hurts,\n\nBy no means can I heal them."},{"align":"center","text":"For the placing of blame turns the shoulder,\n\nAnd reluctancy hinders the heart."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet perfect love casts out fear,\n\nAnd the one who truly knows Me trusts\n\nIn My ways and embraces My correction...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-broken-and-the-proud","num":121,"title":"The Broken and the Proud","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"The broken sinner who repents, I know. Yet the prideful man who considers himself righteous, I do not know. Indeed, he shall be found a liar in the Day of Reckoning. For there is none righteous, no not one, save The Son of Man only.\n\n\nTherefore I ask you, shall the broken sinner be justified in his need, in his fervent desire? He shall indeed be justified in My sight! For I shall clothe him with righteousness and cover him with grace. In his times of weakness My strength shall sustain him, and in My love shall he be made whole. Behold, by My life is he healed!\n\nYet the proud resist Me, and the arrogant want no part with Me as I truly am. For they have clothed themselves with the glory of men, a quickly fading flower. Their comfort is in their riches, and their solace is in their accomplishments, which shall leave them soiled and bruised in the day of their calamity, says The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-love-of-the-truth","num":122,"title":"The Love of The Truth","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Truth is self-evident in the eyes\n\nOf all those who love The Truth."},{"align":"center","text":"Indeed, it resounds within the ears of all those\n\nWho have received of The Truth,\n\nIn whom My spirit dwells...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"uncovered","num":123,"title":"Uncovered","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Truth is evident in My eyes, and a lie is never hidden. Therefore, let no one place their unrighteous cause upon the backs of the children, when a wrong is accounted only to the one who performed it. Neither let the disobedience of the one be covered over by the needs of the many. For I have seen it; lo, all is known to Me.\n\nTherefore let My people be tested, let them be refined in the fire, that the quality of their trust and the endurance of their belief may be revealed, says The Holy One of Israel."}]},{"id":"the-holy-place","num":124,"title":"The Holy Place","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Beloved, there is a language of which\n\nYou know nothing about, says The Lord...\n\n\n\nA language which is pure and beautiful,\n\nA language in need of no words at all;\n\nA language which you shall soon come to know,\n\nA language which I have revealed\n\nTo My servant already...\n\n\n\nA language of overwhelming love, pure and undefiled,\n\nBringing forth much understanding;\n\nA language of power and great glory,\n\nIn which all My servants shall come to stand...\n\n\n\nThe unspoken Word of God received in the presence\n\nOf The Almighty, The Holiest of Holies,\n\nRevealing the essence of who I am...\n\n\n\nUnion in The Spirit of God...\n\n\n\nA place beyond time and space, beyond the knowledge\n\nContained within creation, surpassing all boundaries,\n\nA place even angels long to know...\n\n\n\nThe place where I am and have always been seated,\n\nWhere you shall be also...\n\n\n\nA place without time, The Eternal,\n\nThe Bosom of The Father, of which I AM...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord YahuShua."}]},{"id":"a-return-to-the-garden","num":125,"title":"A Return to the Garden","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"_Thus says The Lord:_ Behold, The Morning Star is risen, the universe is filled with His glory! And that glory shall abide with men, even in them and among them. I shall be a Father unto them, and they shall be My beloved children, forever! Lo, a return to innocence, paradise lost is paradise found, a return to the garden, the universe your playground."},{"align":"center","text":"Thus as I have spoken, so shall it be done:"},{"align":"center","text":"The mystery of God revealed,\n\nThe counting of days no more..."},{"align":"center","text":"Forever young in the presence\n\nOf your Shepherd, your Redeemer,\n\nYour Father, your Brother,\n\nYour Most Beloved Friend,\n\nThe Fulfillment of all things\n\nFor which your hearts have groaned..."},{"align":"center","text":"I AM THE MEANING OF LIFE!..."},{"align":"center","text":"And all who live in Me, and I in them,\n\nWILL LIVE FOREVER!"}]},{"id":"reformation","num":126,"title":"Reformation","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Why does the heathen rage and shake his fist toward Heaven? Behold, he shall fall with none to catch him, and great shall be his fall! Yet the one who reaches for Me shall be lifted up, and the one who extends the hand shall know My dwelling place."},{"align":"center","text":"For as it is written:"},{"align":"center","text":"Whoever has, to him more will be given,\n\nAnd he shall have an abundance..."},{"align":"center","text":"But whoever does not have,\n\nEven what he has shall be taken away, {{ref:Matthew 13:12}}\n\nUntil the Time of Reformation is complete...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-kingdom","num":127,"title":"The Kingdom","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"The Kingdom of God is a garden..."},{"align":"center","text":"Set apart from the many schemes of the adversary,\n\nA place of rest free of briers and thorns..."},{"align":"center","text":"A Sabbath..."},{"align":"center","text":"A holy place which shall never pass away,\n\nWhere no one lies down in death,\n\nNor shall any be made to slumber..."},{"align":"center","text":"My people shall never be covered over again,\n\nFor the old order of things has passed away!\n\nBehold, all things have become new!...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-word-of-truth","num":128,"title":"The Word of Truth","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"My Word is truth! And that which requires understanding shall be given to those of a contrite heart and a humble spirit. For those who love Me obey My Commandments, and those who remember My Sabbaths honor Me and shall know Wisdom. Therefore consider these things carefully."},{"align":"center","text":"For I have indeed prepared\na place for those who seek Me,\n\nFor those who long to know Me as I truly am..."},{"align":"center","text":"A place for all those accepted in The Beloved,\n\nIn whom My spirit dwells..."},{"align":"center","text":"The Kingdom without end...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"faith-without-works-is-dead","num":129,"title":"Faith Without Works Is Dead","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Let all those who truly know Me\n\nProclaim My name first by their ways,\n\nThen with their mouths..."},{"align":"center","text":"For honor only spoken of is but wind,\n\nThe veil of the hypocrite who knows not\n\nWhere he is going, having no remorse\n\nOver where he has been...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"faith-and-works","num":130,"title":"Faith AND Works","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"What is faith without works?\n\nNothing, a lie spoken in vain.\n\n\n\nAnd what of works without faith?\n\nVanity, a false good covering a heart\n\nWhich has turned from The Truth...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"just","num":131,"title":"Just","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"The justice of God is beyond question,\n\nStanding forever in its permanency,\n\nUnwavering for all time...\n\n\n\nRighteous."}]},{"id":"god-is-sovereign","num":132,"title":"God Is Sovereign","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"God is sovereign, His judgment stands."},{"align":"center","text":"Therefore, let the penitent be rewarded equally\n\nTo their forgiveness, which is equal."},{"align":"center","text":"And let all evil unrepented be punished in accordance\n\nWith evil’s deeds, the final penalty of which\n\nHas remained equal even to this day."},{"align":"center","text":"The Lord does not change."}]},{"id":"intentions","num":133,"title":"Intentions","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Where there are righteous works, there are also those\n\nWho seek to spoil them for the sake of pride and envy.\n\nAnd where there is pure knowledge, there are also\n\nThose who defile it among women.\n\n\n\nYet the ignorance of the meek is no cause for offense,\n\nNor shall the error of the humble bring forth rebuke.\n\n\n\nFor I know the heart and look upon the innermost intentions...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"forgive","num":134,"title":"Forgive","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Blessed are those who do not return\n\nEvil for evil, or reviling for reviling,\n\nBut rather pray for their enemies."},{"align":"center","text":"Blessed are those who hold no ill-will\n\nIn their heart toward another."},{"align":"center","text":"Indeed, blessed are all those who\n\nForgive everyone who has sinned against them."},{"align":"center","text":"For great shall be their reward in Heaven...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"a-heavy-stone","num":135,"title":"A Heavy Stone","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Those who refuse My correction are foolish,\n\nAnd must walk through dry places."},{"align":"center","text":"And those who refuse to repent have\n\nSecured their place in the valley of death."},{"align":"center","text":"For the pride of man is a heavy stone,\n\nWhich increases by weight each day\n\nIt remains unbroken...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"insolent-cords","num":136,"title":"Insolent Cords","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Insolent cords bind the proud,\n\nAnd rebellion is a rope by which\n\nThe foolish hang themselves...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-word-of-god","num":137,"title":"The Word of God","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"The Lord your God is a consuming fire, My every word a purifying flame! The presence of The Lord is an oppressive storm, which abases the proud and causes the high-minded to flee! And that which I have spoken to this generation, is it not a sword with which I shall strike to the heart of this people?! For I shall surely set all these crooked paths straight, and burn away the dross!"},{"align":"center","text":"Yet for those who trust in Me and in whom My spirit dwells,\n\nMy words are like a strong tower set in the midst of battle,\n\nWhich can in no wise be broken down!...\n\n\n\nA great trumpet blowing upon the hill outside the city,\n\nWhich echoes throughout the waste places!\n\nA waving banner for this generation, a bright light,\n\nA beacon, shining in the midst of this present darkness!...\n\n\n\nA rod of justice for the oppressed and the persecuted,\n\nA loosening of the chains placed upon My people,\n\nThe breaking apart of every shackle!...\n\n\n\nFreedom for those who love Me,\n\nDeliverance for those who understand,\n\nStrength for the weak, grace to the humble,\n\nManna to nourish the penitent...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"my-witnesses-and-my-word","num":138,"title":"My Witnesses and My Word","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"_Thus says The Lord:_ My words shall be as fire in the mouths of My witnesses, singeing the ears of every hearer! My words shall carry the full weight of My spirit and be very heavy!"},{"align":"center","text":"Behold, I shall cause My words to have weight and power!..."},{"align":"center","text":"Weight as a man feels when struggling against the power of the sea,\n\nThe waves pushing him backward, toppling him, throwing him down,\n\nUntil he has no more breath left in him..."},{"align":"center","text":"As the wind knocked out of a man\n\nWhen he has been struck hard upon the chest,\n\nLeaving him in stunned silence, unable to speak,\n\nFor all his thoughts have departed from him..."},{"align":"center","text":"FOR I SHALL CAUSE MY STRENGTH TO DWELL\n\nIN MY WORDS LIKE THE ROARING OF THE SEA!"}]},{"id":"pride","num":139,"title":"Pride","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Only those who know they are sick\n\nSeek out The Physician."},{"align":"center","text":"Yet those who perceive themselves as well\n\nWill in no wise come to Me, keeping Me at bay;\n\nThey remain seated firmly in the darkness\n\nOf their own understanding,\n\nResting upon their laurels by which\n\nThey have highly esteemed themselves...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"stained-glass","num":140,"title":"Stained Glass","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"One who peers through stained glass can not behold\n\nHis own image, nor is he able to see those inside clearly;\n\nFor he sees only an outline, a blur of color obscuring his vision.\n\n\n\nAnd those on the inside who peer outward remain blinded,\n\nAble to perceive only a shadow of what truly is,\n\nHolding up the hand against the brightness,\n\nFor fear of the noonday sun which is about to come in.\n\n\n\nThus they prefer the light filtered and the brilliance masked,\n\nBy means of all this painted glass.\n\n\n\nWhat then shall a people such as this do when night has fallen?...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-humble-penitent-man","num":141,"title":"The Humble, Penitent Man","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"It is the humble, penitent man\n\nWho gives Me glory in all his ways;\n\nFor he seeks to honor Me,\n\nTo please Me above all else."},{"align":"center","text":"He wants no part in the ways of this world,\n\nNeither does he seek glory for himself;\n\nBy his actions he shines forth,\n\nSeeking glory for The One alone who is God."},{"align":"center","text":"Thus the man who places Me foremost,\n\nIn all things, shall also be first\n\nWhen The Glory comes...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"the-king-eternal","num":142,"title":"The King Eternal","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Behold, the footsteps of The Lord shake the earth! The footsteps of The Lord shall tread the winepress of the wrath of His fury! The presence of The Lord shall break apart the tall mountains; His power shall bring down every mountain, every high place shall be brought low! For the presence of The Lord is strong and mighty, and the anger of The Lord is hot and burns in the heat of His jealousy! Who can turn back The Lord’s anger, once it is kindled? Who can prevent The Most High from performing His will?! Whose glory is like The Lord’s?!\n\nWho comes as The King above all kings wearing the raiment of God, whose majesty is beyond compare?! Who is able to stand in the day of His wrath, or survive the power of His sword which proceeds from His mouth, the day He strikes through the heart of all people and lays His enemies waste, the day every adversary is consumed in the brightness of His coming?! For He is mighty in battle and His justice is swift, His victory absolute!"},{"align":"center","text":"Who is The King of Glory?!"},{"align":"center","text":"YahuShua HaMashiach, HE is The King of Glory!\n\nHis power is infinite, His love never-ending!"},{"align":"center","text":"HE is The King Everlasting,\n\nThe King of Righteousness!"},{"align":"center","text":"His grace is shed abroad to\n\nEvery contrite and humble spirit;\n\nHis forgiveness is pure, ever-flowing\n\nInto the hearts of the penitent,\n\nRestoring them to righteousness and life!"},{"align":"center","text":"Yes, He is The One and Only King Eternal!\n\nThere is no other, there is none like Him!"}]},{"id":"in-union-with-the-messiah","num":143,"title":"In Union With The Messiah","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"Beloved, there is a day coming when you shall enter My presence and never leave it, a day when you shall behold My face, says The Lord. And wheresoever your heart leads you, there will I be also, with you always where you are. Whether you journey to the heights of the mountains, or to the farthest reaches of creation, there I am, with you where you are. Beloved, all creation is Mine, and all I have is yours. For you are Mine, even as I am yours also... _Together, forever._\n\n\nFor the glory you have seen, and that which you have imagined, has until now been measured in a human way. Yet the glory of The Lord is of such a kind! Glory which has always been, glory with no beginning and no end, having neither height, nor depth, nor length, nor width. For My glory is life and that love we share, a gift of understanding which comes by knowledge of The Holy; glory which can not yet be fully realized, nor are there words sufficient to open your understanding... _Fulfillment, which only comes by union._"}]},{"id":"my-love-endures-forever","num":144,"title":"My Love Endures Forever","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"Long after the glory of men has passed away, with the height\n\nOf their kingdoms turned to dust, My love endures!\n\n\n\nLong after the stars you behold in the heavens\n\nHave ceased from shining, My love endures!\n\n\n\nDeeper and wider than space and time, My love endures!\n\n\n\nEven before creation, My love endures; and after, My love remains.\n\n\n\nFor I shall be your God, and you shall be My people,\n\nAs long as My love endures...\n\n\n\nSays The Lord."}]},{"id":"i-am-god","num":145,"title":"I AM GOD","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"I am He who formed the earth and all you see in the heavens, He who set the foundations and called creation forth by the Word of His power and the vastness of His knowledge, causing all things to be!\n\nI made the matrix, and set all things in order; I am He who formed it! I know all the hidden parts; even the most minute detail, by which all things are made, is known to Me! Behold, I see the inward parts; from the innermost depths to that which can not be seen by man, all is known to Me!\n\nBefore Me is the whole of creation at all times! No distance is far from Me, no measure is too great for Me, and no weight is too heavy. That which is beyond your comprehension is known to Me each morning, and every evening I behold the whole of creation and consider. For I am The Lord. YAHUWAH is My name."}]},{"id":"the-volumes-of-truth","num":146,"title":"The Volumes of Truth","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"_Thus says The Lord:_ Beloved, this Word, even every Volume to every Letter, is the Word of My glory, which I have put forth once again - A testament of My love and sacrifice, the announcement of My coming, a proclamation of truth, revelation of who I really am! The Trumpet Call of God, so all those called and chosen may hear and come to Me in their proper time and season.\n\nBehold, it is also a strong correction for all those who have taken to themselves MY name and MY Word, to pollute it, a plumb line for this wicked generation! For this Word is a waving banner, an ensign to all nations! - A trumpet of alarm and war, the sound of recompense and judgment, which shall soon fall upon every nation!"},{"align":"center","text":"For I AM WHO I AM!\n\nThe Only Begotten of The Father!\n\nThe One True God and Savior!\n\nThe Mashiach!..."},{"align":"center","text":"YAHUSHUA-YAHUWAH!"}]},{"id":"keep-watch","num":147,"title":"Keep Watch","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"_Thus declares The Lord:_ All your setting of dates shall come to nothing, and all your precise predictions shall fail, for I may take them before or after. For I am God.\n\nBehold, the first election is made, the time of bundling passed. Thick clouds have risen in the west, the hard rains have come, and who in all the earth is able to prevent it as it draws near, or hinder it when it arrives? Lo, a mighty wind blows in the east, yet who is aware of it until it has overtaken them?\n\nTherefore keep watch, for you know not the time of The Lord’s coming. Whether it be in the first, or in the second, or in the third watch of the night, you know not the time of His return. You know not the day or the hour, says The Lord."}]},{"id":"awaken","num":148,"title":"AWAKEN","paragraphs":[{"align":"justify","text":"The mountains tremble and the hills quiver, the oxen grumble in their stalls and the lambs leap about in their places. FOR I AM COME.\n\nDo you hear the sound of My heart pounding within My chest, the thunder rumbling as the storm approaches? Look how the lightning flashes upon the southern skies, see how the clouds roil on the western horizon. Behold, the northern lands are anxious, the isles of the east are unsettled and the deserts burn with hatred. FOR I AM COME.\n\nBehold, the trumpet is blown in the four corners, the warning broadcast in all the earth, and still you sleep! AWAKEN! I AM COME! Says The Lord."}]},{"id":"a-psalm-of-david","num":149,"title":"A Psalm of David","paragraphs":[{"align":"center","text":"YahuShua is my shepherd; I shall not want.\n\nHe makes me lie down in green pastures,\n\nHe leads me beside still waters, He restores my soul.\n\nHe leads me in paths of righteousness, for His name’s sake.\n\nYea, though I walk through the valley of the shadow\n\nOf death, I will fear no evil, for You are with me;\n\nYour rod and Your staff, they comfort me.\n\nYou prepare a table before me in the presence\n\nOf my enemies, you anoint my head with oil,\n\nMy cup runs over.\n\nSurely goodness and mercy shall follow me\n\nAll the days of my life, and I will dwell\n\nIn the house of YAHUWAH, forever."}]}];
